, but, what, Musk built a high-frequency-trading Dogecoin bot?


  [4] The complaint disagrees, arguing that Musk=E2=80=99s own efforts make=
 Dogecoin security-like: =E2=80=9CThe enterprise is common because the digi=
tal =E2=80=98ecosystem=E2=80=99 or network around the Dogecoin blockchain c=
onsists of developers, nodes, and miners working together to develop, maint=
ain, and secure the blockchain; and because the success of the ecosystem dr=
ives demand for Dogecoin and thus determines investors=E2=80=99 profits, in=
 the form of increased value of Dogecoin. The enterprise is also common bec=
ause Musk=E2=80=99s advisor, Billy Markus is, and Musk=E2=80=99s 'right-han=
d man,' Jared Birchall was, a member of the Dogecoin Foundation, Inc. (=E2=
=80=98DCFI=E2=80=99) Board of Advisors; and because Musk, the Dogecoin core=
 developers, as well as the DCFI Board Advisors, help publicize Dogecoin th=
rough social media content and by giving interviews to the press. The chara=
cter Dogecoin is given in commerce by the publicity efforts of Defendant Mu=
sk, is of a fun, profitable and fungible investment instrument with immense=
 long-term utility both as a store of wealth and as a medium of exchange, o=
n the cutting edge of technology and pop culture. The investor is led to ex=
pect profits from the computing efforts of developers, nodes, and miners; f=
rom Musk=E2=80=99s consulting with the core developers; from the publicity =
efforts of Musk, DCFI, and various online shills or =E2=80=98influencers;=
=E2=80=99 and the crypto exchanges offering Dogecoin to investors.=E2=80=9D


  [5] Or: There is a claim about insider trading, that =E2=80=9CMusk traded=
 Dogecoin profitably through one or more wallets and domestic exchanges usi=
ng foreknowledge then unknown and undisclosed to Dogecoin investors general=
ly or publicly, of his own intended moves to manipulate the market.=E2=80=
=9D But his moves were tweets! How can it be illegal insider trading to tra=
de ahead of your own plans to tweet a joke?


  [6] Incidentally, I realize that he is  not technically the chief executi=
ve officer of Twitter anymore, but we are all grown-ups here, and he runs T=
witter. Still I suppose that Twitter=E2=80=99s incoming CEO, Linda Yaccarin=
o, could get out ahead of this by proposing an IPO herself.=20


