<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Dogecoin is a tradable electronic=C2=A0token r=
epresenting the value of Elon Musk=E2=80=99s attention. When Elon Musk twee=
ts about Dogecoin, its price goes up. When he goes on =E2=80=9CSaturday Nig=
ht Live=E2=80=9D and makes painful jokes about Dogecoin, its value goes up.=
<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; t=
ext-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-co=
lor: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: trans=
parent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0When Elon Musk does not shine the bright light of his attention o=
n Dogecoin, its value drifts down.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is not <em>entirely=C2=A0</em>true =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0somebody traded Dogecoin even before Elon Musk paid attention to i=
t =E2=80=94=C2=A0but it=E2=80=99s a reasonable model. It is not investment =
advice, though it does seem to have been a large part of <a href=3D"https:/=
/link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31696643.267418/aHR0cHM6Ly90d2l0dGVy=
LmNvbS9BbGFtZWRhVHJhYnVjY28vc3RhdHVzLzEzODUxODEwNDg1MDIzMjkzNDk/607f07ceef4=
b8524a319a23cB9643c522" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" targ=
et=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bo=
rder-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: =
solid; background-color: #ccc;"> the investing approach</a>=C2=A0of Alameda=
 Research, which was a multibillion-dollar crypto trading firm for a while.=
 If you are a crypto hedge fund, or a retail crypto trader, this model woul=
d suggest that you should buy Dogecoin just before Musk tweets about it and=
 sell it a bit after he tweets, but that=E2=80=99s hard (you have to know w=
hen he=E2=80=99ll tweet). A second-best model might be to buy Dogecoin shor=
tly after Musk tweets about it and then sell it a bit later, and that does =
seem to <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31696643.2=
67418/aHR0cHM6Ly90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS9BbGFtZWRhVHJhYnVjY28vc3RhdHVzLzEzODIyNDQxM=
zk0NDI0NzUwMTU/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc2d8d5a0" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" it=
emscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decor=
ation: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000=
000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> have been Alamed=
a=E2=80=99s approach</a>.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But what if you are Elon Musk? A thing exists =
in the world whose value depends entirely on Elon Musk=E2=80=99s tweets, an=
d you are Elon Musk. What is the trade here, for you? I mean! From first pr=
inciples:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Buy a ton of it.</li>=09<li style=3D"=
margin-bottom: 5px;">Tweet about it.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px=
;">Sell a ton of it.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is almost too dumb to write because the o=
pportunity=C2=A0is so obvious, but at the same time the opportunity is so r=
are that you might somehow not think of it. I <a href=3D"https://link.mail.=
bloombergbusiness.com/click/31696643.267418/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmN=
vbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDUtMTcvZWxvbi1tdXNrLWNvbnRyb2xzLWJpdGNvaW=
4tYW5kLWRvZ2Vjb2luLXByaWNlcy13aXRoLXB1cmUtbWFnaWM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDYwNTIzX01PT=
kVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09=
MjMwNjA1JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBdb514e6c"=
 itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"=
color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px;=
 border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color=
: #ccc;">  once wrote about this trade</a> that it was as though someone ha=
nded Musk a lamp and told him there was a genie inside of it, and that =E2=
=80=9Cany time you want the price of [Dogecoin] to go up or down by 10% or =
more, you can just whisper =E2=80=98price go up=E2=80=99 or =E2=80=98price =
go down=E2=80=99 into the lamp, and it will happen instantly. You are the o=
nly person who can do this, and you can do it as often as you want=E2=80=9D=
:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I just think that if you presented=
 this possibility to any famous investor throughout history they would abso=
lutely faint with excitement. And here Musk is, the second-richest person i=
n the world, either doing it =E2=80=94=C2=A0in which case it=E2=80=99s one =
of the greatest trades, and also one of the greatest trolls, in history =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0or=C2=A0<em>not=C2=A0</em>doing it, rubbing the lamp and making=
 Bitcoin and Dogecoin go up and down and up and down and up and down with h=
is whims,=C2=A0<em>just=C2=A0</em>for fun, leaving billions of dollars of p=
rofit on the table because he doesn=E2=80=99t need the money and has the pu=
rest imaginable commitment to internet trolling.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Oh yeah: I assumed that Musk was=C2=A0<em>not=
=C2=A0</em>doing this obvious trade.=C2=A0He was certainly tweeting about D=
ogecoin, and he had certainly bought some Dogecoin, but I just figured that=
 he was not in fact optimizing his financial returns on the trading-plus-tw=
eeting.=C2=A0He was busy running Tesla and SpaceX and the tunnel thing and =
probably several other companies at the time (this was pre-Twitter); his wh=
ole schtick was about building stuff, not just dumb manipulation of meaning=
less abstract financial markets. Still the opportunity was so obvious!</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway here=E2=80=99s an amazing lawsuit claim=
ing=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31696643.=
267418/aHR0cHM6Ly9hc3NldHMuYndieC5pby9kb2N1bWVudHMvdXNlcnMvaXFqV0hCRmRmeElV=
L3JkZEU0bVhLanZHdy92MA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBdef2cc8b" itemprop=3D"Story=
Link" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; te=
xt-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-col=
or: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">he was ma=
nipulating Dogecoin to make money</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is a securities fraud class action arisin=
g from a deliberate course of carnival barking market manipulation and insi=
der trading by the world=E2=80=99s richest man Elon Musk, who hijacked an e=
mergent pop-culture phenomenon to cross-promote himself and his companies, =
and to pad his obscene fortune, preying on the earnest hopes of vulnerable =
Americans, including war veterans, blue collar workers, and the elderly. ..=
.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Musk=E2=80=99s followers did exactly what he s=
aid. Musk=E2=80=99s pretense that promotion of Dogecoin was just well-meani=
ng fun=E2=80=94not meant to be taken seriously=E2=80=94is not credible. It =
is Musk=E2=80=99s custom=C2=A0to publicly address serious topics glibly on =
Twitter. That doesn=E2=80=99t make him any less serious. Musk knows that th=
e bulk of his followers are not sophisticated in business or investment, an=
d Musk uses this knowledge to manipulate them. Musk is what is called an ap=
ex predator, feeding on and manipulating the hordes below, including his Tw=
itter following which has grown to 141 million.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The complaint claims that he made $10.2 billio=
n of profit on Dogecoin from just one of his several wallets, an amount tha=
t is bigger than=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cl=
ick/31696643.267418/aHR0cHM6Ly9jb2lubWFya2V0Y2FwLmNvbS9jdXJyZW5jaWVzL2RvZ2V=
jb2luLw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB02ec43c0" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">the entire current marke=
t capitalization of Dogecoin</a>. (Which makes sense: If Dogecoin is valued=
 based on Musk=E2=80=99s attention, he should have extracted more than it i=
s currently worth.) Also=C2=A0it is just a big number? Like if you went to =
Elon Musk and said =E2=80=9Chere is a dumb thing that you could do to make =
$100 million in 10 minutes,=E2=80=9D he might reasonably say=C2=A0=E2=80=9C=
nah I have so much money, $100 million is not enough to make me spend 10 mi=
nutes doing a dumb thing.=E2=80=9D But $10 billion is so=C2=A0much more mon=
ey than that! If you went=C2=A0to Elon Musk and said=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cyou can =
do some dumb tweets to make $10 billion,=E2=80=9D=C2=A0might he say yes?</p=
>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Now, there are some problems with this lawsuit=
.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"color: #000000; =
text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-c=
olor: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: tran=
sparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a>=C2=A0The most obvious problem is that the wallet the plaintiffs have i=
dentified =E2=80=94=C2=A0the one that made $10.2 billion of profits trading=
 Dogecoin based on Musk=E2=80=99s tweets, and that at one point held over $=
25 billion of Dogecoin=C2=A0=E2=80=94=C2=A0probably does not actually belon=
g=C2=A0to him. The evidence that the plaintiffs cite is pretty thin:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Dogecoin wallet DH5yaieqoZN36fDVciNyRueRGvGLR3=
mr7L (=E2=80=9CDH5ya=E2=80=9D) also belongs to Defendant Musk. ...=C2=A0On =
February 10, 2021, Musk tweeted that he had purchased Dogecoin for his son.=
 =E2=80=A6 The previous day, DH5ya (which was then the world=E2=80=99s larg=
est Dogecoin wallet, containing roughly $2.8 billion worth of Dogecoin) pla=
ced a transaction for 28.061971 Dogecoins, the numeric equivalent of Defend=
ant Musk=E2=80=99s date of birth, i.e., the 28th of June 1971. This wallet =
would purchase Dogecoin in that same amount on February 10, 2021, and once =
again on February 17th. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">DH5ya was opened on February 5, 2019, less tha=
n two months before Musk began publicly promoting Dogecoin on Twitter when =
Dogecoin was trading at $0.0018 (less than two-tenths of a cent per coin). =
=E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">By February 3, 2021, on the eve of Musk=E2=80=
=99s most intense period of Dogecoin promotion and the bull market it immed=
iately gave rise to, DH5ya had accumulated almost 35 billion Dogecoins and =
was the largest Dogecoin wallet in existence.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In a <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbus=
iness.com/click/31696643.267418/aHR0cHM6Ly9hc3NldHMuYndieC5pby9kb2N1bWVudHM=
vdXNlcnMvaXFqV0hCRmRmeElVL3JBUU5IaVl0RG9Wdy92MA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB29=
55211c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" st=
yle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-widt=
h: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgroun=
d-color: #ccc;"> previous version of their lawsuit</a>, from last December,=
 they cited additional, uh, evidence:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There are many cryptic messages hidden in the =
transactions of this wallet which prove it belongs to Musk.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Three separate transactions were made with thi=
s wallet in the following amount: 28.061971 Dogecoin's, which reference Elo=
n Musk's birthday of June 28, 1971.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There have been transactions with exactly 69 c=
oins (more than 6 times) and exactly 420 coins (2 times) which are numbers =
that Musk often references in furtherance of his trademark crude humor (69 =
for sex and 420 for marijuana).</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">8.95121514 coins, when converted to letters sa=
ys, "Hi Elon."</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">1.3371337 coins, 1337 meaning "extremely skill=
ed (at gaming or computing) and 80085 coins which says =E2=80=9CBOOBS=E2=80=
=9D in keeping with Musk=E2=80=99s crude sense of humor.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Look: Is Elon Musk a guy who would buy things =
in units of 80,085 because that's how you type =E2=80=9CBOOBS=E2=80=9D on a=
 calculator? Maybe? He likes number jokes; he once pretended he was going t=
o take Tesla Inc. private at <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/31696643.267418/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2Fy=
dGljbGVzLzIwMTgtMDgtMDgvZWxvbi1tdXNrLWhhcy1zb21lLWZ1bi13aXRoLXRlc2xhP2NtcGl=
kPUJCRDA2MDUyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbG=
V0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDYwNSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b85=
24a319a23cB5e4b3322" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">  $420 per share</a>, and then really did tak=
e Twitter Inc. private at <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.co=
m/click/31696643.267418/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGl=
jbGVzLzIwMjItMDQtMjYvZWxvbi1nb3QtaGlzLWRlYWw_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDYwNTIzX01PTkVZU1=
RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwN=
jA1JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBd945396f" item=
prop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color=
: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bord=
er-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #cc=
c;">  $54.20 per share</a>. But are there lots of guys like that? Oh yes; E=
lon Musk did not invent typing =E2=80=9C80085=E2=80=9D on a calculator. Are=
 some of the guys who make these jokes doing so=C2=A0because they are imita=
ting Elon Musk? Absolutely. If you are doing Dogecoin transactions that spe=
ll out =E2=80=9CHi Elon,=E2=80=9D is it more likely that (1) you are Elon M=
usk or (2) you=E2=80=99re an Elon Musk super-fan and want to say hi to him?=
 Is it not weird to say hi to yourself?=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway in their <a href=3D"https://link.mail.b=
loombergbusiness.com/click/31696643.267418/aHR0cHM6Ly9hc3NldHMuYndieC5pby9k=
b2N1bWVudHMvdXNlcnMvaXFqV0hCRmRmeElVL3JVRWgzRkxMWm1Fcy92MA/607f07ceef4b8524=
a319a23cB6e5689d3" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D=
"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-=
bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid=
; background-color: #ccc;"> response to the previous version of the lawsuit=
</a>, filed in March, Musk=E2=80=99s lawyers denied that he owns that walle=
t:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That wallet does not=C2=A0belong t=
o Mr. Musk, and indeed the website that Plaintiffs relied upon in their Fir=
st Amended Complaint ... states that the wallet in question belongs to Robi=
nhood, a large consumer-facing exchange that permits retail buyers to buy a=
nd sell cryptocurrencies, including<br />Dogecoin.=C2=A0Plaintiffs speculat=
e that the wallet belongs to Mr. Musk solely because some small deposits to=
 the account (which any member of the public can make) are for amounts that=
 Plaintiffs claim are associated with Mr. Musk, such as =E2=80=9C69=E2=80=
=9D or =E2=80=9C420=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9CHi Elon=E2=80=9D in numbers.</p></=
blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Ah well.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#f=
ootnote-3" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: non=
e !important; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-blo=
ck;">
<span>[3]</span>
</a>=C2=A0If Musk=C2=A0<em>wasn=E2=80=99t=C2=A0</em>selling piles of Dogeco=
in as his tweets drove up the price, then the case for market manipulation =
seems pretty weak. Trolling, sure, but market manipulation, probably not.</=
p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Still there are other problems with the lawsui=
t. One problem is that the plaintiffs are=C2=A0suing Musk for insider tradi=
ng and securities fraud, which only works if Dogecoin is a security. Is it?=
 Well. <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31696643.26=
7418/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDktMD=
gvZ2FyeS1nZW5zbGVyLXdhbnRzLXRvLXJlZ3VsYXRlLWNyeXB0bz9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNjA1MjNfT=
U9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVy=
bT0yMzA2MDUmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBac23a1=
32" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">  Almost every cryptocurrency</a>, other than Bitcoin and mayb=
e Ether, is probably a security under US securities law, <a href=3D"https:/=
/link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31696643.267418/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxv=
b21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDItMTMvdGhlLXNlYy1jcmFja3MtZG9=
3bi1vbi1jcnlwdG8_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDYwNTIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbC=
Z1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwNjA1JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25le=
XN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBcdea89a9" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  at least</a> in the vi=
ew of the US Securities and Exchange Commission (which I think is mostly co=
rrect). But Dogecoin? The rule is that =E2=80=9Cthe investment of money in =
a common enterprise with a reasonable expectation of profits to be derived =
from the efforts of others=E2=80=9D makes something a security, and virtual=
ly every crypto project, with its promise of wealth from some blockchain ec=
osystem, probably qualifies. Except Dogecoin! Dogecoin is just a joke about=
 a dog. The guys who invented it were explicitly joking, and have <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31696643.267418/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cuY25iYy5jb20vMjAyMS8wNy8xNC9kb2dlY29pbi1jby1jcmVhdG9yLWphY2tzb24tcGFs=
bWVyLWNyaXRpY2l6ZXMtdGhlLWNyeXB0by1pbmR1c3RyeS5odG1s/607f07ceef4b8524a319a2=
3cB00a973a5" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blan=
k" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom=
-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; back=
ground-color: #ccc;"> gone around telling people</a> it is stupid. This is =
not a crypto token that was sold to raise money to build out a blockchain e=
nterprise. It is a pure joke with no enterprise at all, which makes it prob=
ably not a security.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-4" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; ba=
ckground-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[4]</span>
</a></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">An even bigger problem is just, like, what wou=
ld it=C2=A0<em>mean=C2=A0</em>for Elon Musk to=C2=A0<em>manipulate </em>Dog=
ecoin?<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-5" style=3D"color: #000=
000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bot=
tom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color:=
 transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[5]</span>
</a>=C2=A0Like a classic form of market manipulation is:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You buy some penny stock.</li>=09<li =
style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You tweet that the company discovered a cure =
for cancer.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You are lying.</li>=09=
<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">People believe you.</li>=09<li style=3D"m=
argin-bottom: 5px;">The stock goes up.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5=
px;">You sell the stock.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There is some <em>dishonesty</em>; you say som=
ething that is not true, to trick people into buying the stock. But apply t=
hat to Dogecoin:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Elon Musk buys some Dogecoin.</li>=09=
<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">He tweets, like, a picture of a Shiba Inu=
 or whatever.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">People are like =E2=
=80=9Cooh Elon Musk is paying attention to Dogecoin.=E2=80=9D</li>=09<li st=
yle=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The price goes up.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-b=
ottom: 5px;">He sells Dogecoin.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That=E2=80=99s the claim in this lawsuit, thou=
gh Musk denies it. But=C2=A0even if it were true, where is the lie here? Do=
gecoin goes up and down based on Elon Musk=E2=80=99s attention, so when he =
tweets about it, the market <em>correctly</em> concludes that=C2=A0Elon Mus=
k is paying attention to it, and the price goes up. From the complaint:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On July 17, 2020, Musk tweeted a meme of a pho=
to of a dust storm overtaking an urban area, with the face of the Dogecoin =
Shiba Inu superimposed on the dust cloud. The cloud was labeled =E2=80=9Cdo=
gecoin standard.=E2=80=9D The urban area about to be overtaken was labelled=
, =E2=80=9Cglobal financial system.=E2=80=9D Above this image, Musk superim=
posed the remark, =E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s inevitable.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Immediately following this tweet, Dogecoin=E2=
=80=99s price rose 14%, from $0.00304 to $0.00363, in less than two hours.<=
/p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On December 20, 2020, Musk tweeted, =E2=80=9CO=
ne word: Doge.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This tweet caused the price of Dogecoin to inc=
rease by 20%.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On January 28, 2021, Musk tweeted an image of =
a magazine cover parodying Vogue magazine. It was titled =E2=80=9CDogue,=E2=
=80=9D and it featured a dog fashion model. (Exhibit =E2=80=9CJ=E2=80=9D) T=
his tweet caused Dogecoin=E2=80=99s price to shoot from $0.0262 to $0.0799,=
 a 57% increase in just five hours.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In the early hours of February 4, 2021, Musk t=
weeted a picture of a rocket blasting into space with the Moon looming in t=
he background. Beneath this tweet, he added another tweet that read, simply=
: =E2=80=9CDoge.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The price of Dogecoin increased from $0.04089 =
to $0.05797 within an hour.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Later that day, February 4, 2021, Musk tweeted=
 another meme. This was a screen-capture of the famous =E2=80=9CCircle of L=
ife=E2=80=9D scene from Disney=E2=80=99s The Lion King animated film, with =
Dogecoin=E2=80=99s Shiba Inu mascot and Elon Musk superimposed.=C2=A0Above =
this image, Musk added the remark, =E2=80=9Cur welcome=E2=80=9D an apparent=
 reference directed at Dogecoin investors. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On February 24, 2021, Musk tweeted an image of=
 a cartoon Shiba Inu in a spacesuit, on the moon, holding up a flag labelle=
d =E2=80=9CDoge.=E2=80=9D Above this image, Musk added the remark, =E2=80=
=9CLiterally.=E2=80=9D And later he tweeted, =E2=80=9COn the actual moon.=
=E2=80=9D Dogecoin=E2=80=99s price shot up 25% that same day.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Come on! Come on! You could find some humorles=
s quibbles here: Did Elon Musk really believe, and have adequate grounds fo=
r believing, that the =E2=80=9CDogecoin standard=E2=80=9D would swallow the=
 global financial system? But most of these tweets are just pictures of dog=
s. The overall thrust here is that Dogecoin is an online=C2=A0joke, and Elo=
n Musk is a famous person who likes online jokes, and for a time there was =
a valuable synergy there. The value of Dogecoin as an online joke went up w=
hen Elon Musk was making Dogecoin jokes online. If you bought Dogecoin beca=
use Elon Musk tweeted about it, you didn=E2=80=99t buy it=C2=A0because you =
expected it to become the global monetary standard, or because you expected=
 Tesla to start pricing cars in Dogecoin or whatever. You bought it=C2=A0<e=
m>because Elon Musk tweeted about it</em>. That was the whole analysis: =E2=
=80=9CElon Musk tweeted about this joke dog coin, so I=E2=80=99m gonna buy =
it.=E2=80=9D He really did tweet about it! How could you have been misled?<=
/p>
