<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Do you know what else would be a good tradable=
 token of Elon Musk-ness? The stock of Twitter Inc., or X Corp. or whatever=
 they=E2=80=99re calling it these days. But Twitter is closely held since M=
usk and a few friends bought it last year, so retail investors cannot trade=
 it for its meme potential, and Musk=E2=80=99s public pronouncements cannot=
 move its stock.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And so this morning my Bloomberg Opinion colle=
ague Ed Hammond argues that =E2=80=9C<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/31696643.267418/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGlu=
aW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDYtMDUvZm9yLWhpcy1uZXh0LXRyaWNrLWVsb24tbXVzay1zaG9=
1bGQtdGFrZS10d2l0dGVyLXB1YmxpYz9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNjA1MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbW=
VkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzA2MDUmdXRtX2Nhb=
XBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB2e036185" itemprop=3D"Story=
Link" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; te=
xt-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-col=
or: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  For His=
 Next Trick, Musk Should Take Twitter Public</a>.=E2=80=9D The rationale he=
re is not so much that Twitter needs the money (though it does!) or that it=
 makes more sense as a pubic company or whatever, and more that Musk is lea=
ving money on the table by doing meme-stock stuff to a private company:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Whether Musk is launching electric cars, reusi=
ng rockets or just casually pumping crypto, his power to rapidly accumulate=
 goodwill among the masses is unmatched. So why not do it with Twitter, the=
 very organ through which much of that financial loyalty is husbanded?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Sure, big institutional money and much of the =
financial media would question the rationale. But so what? They have been d=
oing that for years about Tesla, and look where that got them. In fact, it =
would probably help. Musk long ago mastered the populist gift for provoking=
 =E2=80=9Cestablishment=E2=80=9D skepticism to push an image of victimhood.=
 ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Going public =E2=80=94 which Musk himself floa=
ted as an idea within as little as three years of taking Twitter private =
=E2=80=94 would also give him the thing he craves constantly: a referendum =
on his superiority. It must be irksome for someone of such undimmed self-lo=
ve to have his project devalued by dumb, mainstream-money institutions. The=
 people would have his back =E2=80=94 I think they would. And even if they =
didn=E2=80=99t right away, he could convince a lot of them. He=E2=80=99s go=
od at that. Twitter would become the ultimate meme stock, a vehicle of perp=
etual contrarianism.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I think this is correct. He should sell the st=
ock at $69 per share, or $420, or $800.85. He should try to get <a href=3D"=
