ory before and already have an allocation. But if you go into an allocator=
=E2=80=99s office and say =E2=80=9Cgive me money so I can buy temperature,=
=E2=80=9D <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31696643=
.267418/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDYtMDE=
vZ29sZG1hbi1hcXItYWx1bW5pLXN0YXJ0LW5pY2hlLW11bHRpc3RyYXQtd2l0aC1hc25lc3MtYm=
Fja2luZz9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNjA1MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb=
3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzA2MDUmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/=
607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf0639fbe" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"item=
scope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !im=
portant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bot=
tom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  that will pique their interest=
</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A new multistrategy hedge fund run by Wall Str=
eet veterans Brian Hurst and Elisha Wiesel began trading Thursday, focusing=
 on offbeat strategies such as temperature arbitrage.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Hurst, a 21-year veteran of AQR Capital Manage=
ment, and Wiesel, who spent 25 years at Goldman Sachs Group Inc., are start=
ing Niche Plus as ClearAlpha Technologies=E2=80=99 first fund. With commitm=
ents of several hundred million dollars, it expects to have $1 billion with=
in a year to deploy across 13 teams running 20 strategies.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CWe=E2=80=99re focusing on what we cal=
l niche alpha strategies, which are going to be off the beaten path,=E2=80=
=9D Hurst, 50, said in an interview at the firm=E2=80=99s Greenwich, Connec=
ticut offices. =E2=80=A6.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">While most multistrategy firms rely heavily on=
 trading stocks in developed markets, Niche Plus=E2=80=99s only traditional=
 long-short stock play focuses on Middle East and North African shares.=C2=
=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">More than half of the fund=E2=80=99s teams run=
 their own firms while managing accounts for ClearAlpha, which has risk con=
trol over those portfolios. One specialized team is made up of former Swiss=
 Re AG traders who run a temperature arbitrage strategy based on the weathe=
r.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CWe identify dislocations where the te=
mperature is high one place and low somewhere else, and then we short the h=
igh temperature and buy the low temperature,=E2=80=9D is probably not the s=
trategy here, though it would be wonderful if it was. Anyway I love the ide=
a of a hedge fund where the rules are (1) you have to make money but (2) yo=
u can=E2=80=99t trade stocks, bonds or crypto. The constraints make the art=
.</p>
